    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Audio Remote Switch Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2067_3.0_jpn_11580675_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Loosen screw (A). Disconnect the coupler (B) and remove the audio remote switch (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Work with care to prevent the screw from falling out."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2067_3.0_jpn_11580676_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Remove the audio remote switch (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Audio Remote switch Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2067_3.0_jpn_11580677_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Measure the resistance between the audio remote switch 12P coupler No. 2 and No. 5 terminals at each position. Measure the resistance between the No. 3 and No. 5 terminals of the audio remote switch 12P coupler at each position. If it is out of the standard value, replace the audio remote switch."
    },
